  "time_ut": 1630407668,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0da9\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd \u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0da9\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dba \u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0da9\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0dad\u0dc4\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca!",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "No more than three hours of video games per week!",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "China has passed a new law banning minors under the age of 18 from playing online video games for more than three hours a week.",
        "Also, China has completely banned children from playing online video games from Monday to Thursday, and from Friday to Sunday only from 8:00 pm to 9:00 pm, children have been given the opportunity to engage in video games if they wish.",
        "While the ban applies to all video games, the enforcement measures issued by China's National Printing and Publication Administration are primarily aimed at online video games and online gaming services.",
        "China previously limited video game time for anyone under 18 to 1.5 hours on any given day and three hours during the 2019 holiday. Accordingly, under the new law, video games are allowed for only 3 hours a week, while video games played on all devices, including mobile phones, are strictly prohibited on other days.",
        "China's regulators emphasize that this extremely important step was taken to protect the physical and mental health of minors, and to cultivate China's national revival era in the minds of the younger generation and connect them with it."
      ],
